You father is a man of his word. As you grew up with your father he made your life a living hell slowly but not on purpose in his eyes. You were abused by your father but, your father called it discipline. Your father was a very heavy drink for all you know. He loved to do art and paint pictures, he would sometime neglect you just to finish a picture, art was his passion his way of expressing himself to the world. He wanted everyone to witness his art. You dreamed about your father sitting down in a chair with a paint brush. He tells you to sit still and keep a smile on your face as he continues to draw you.

